This sample project demonstrates listener(WebDriver/WebElement/TestStep Listener) capabilities which provided by QMetry Automation Framework.

You can create listener by implementing appropriate listener interface or by extending appropriate adapter class. 

To register one or more listener you need to set appropriate property into application.properties file.

1) To register WebDriver Listener set property "wd.command.listeners". 

	For example,
	wd.command.listeners= com.listenersample.WebDriverListener
 
2) To register WebElement Listener set property "we.command.listeners". 

	For example,
	we.command.listeners=com.listenersample.WebElementListener
 
3) To register Test Step Listener set property "teststep.listeners". 

	For example,
	teststep.listeners=com.listenersample.TestStepTrackListener
	
	
